                'about_head_one' => 'JOHNNIE COCHRAN',
                'about_head_two' => 'WAS A HERO TO ME',
                'bio' => '<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgba(249,248,246,0.48); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: bold;">James A. Bryant<span>&nbsp;</span></strong>is a senior attorney for the Cochran Firm – California. James is an experienced trial lawyer with decades of practice in both litigation and transactional law. His primary practice areas are civil rights, employment, and police misconduct.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">As a litigator, James has successfully represented both plaintiffs and defendants in many high profile cases. In addition, James has extensive experience handling entertainment and intellectual property matters. As a transactional attorney, he has negotiated numerous film and television projects, and has expertise in complex business contract law.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;<br></p><div class="content mCustomScrollbar _mCS_1" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><div id="mCSB_1" class="mCustomScrollBox mCS-light" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;"><div class="mCSB_container" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;"><div class="inPara" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;"><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">He began his legal career as an associate at a prestigious San Francisco law firm handling a number of high profile transactional and litigation matters including mergers and acquisitions, investment fund formation and secured transactions. James joined The Cochran Firm – California in 2014, establishing the firm’s entertainment and business division. He has obtained numerous dismissals and nearly $20 million in jury verdicts, arbitration awards and settlements on behalf of his clients in both state and federal courts. James has also been engaged in negotiating a total of more than $1 billion in business transactions.</p><h3 style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 22px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1em; font-weight: 500;">HONORS &amp; AWARDS</h3><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">-Names in list of California Super Lawyers, 2018<br style="box-sizing: border-box;">-Names in California Super Lawyers’s list of Rising Stars, 2015-2018<br style="box-sizing: border-box;">-University of California Berkeley, Student Body Vice President<br style="box-sizing: border-box;">-University of California Student Association,&nbsp;Legislative Lobbyist</p></div></div></div></div>',
                'created_at' => Carbon::now(),
                'updated_at' => Carbon::now(),
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'ANAHITA SEDAGHATFAR',
                'role' => 'OF COUNSEL',
                'avatar' => 'storage/attornys/uHJwIYqeRGa47J2ErwLCd4qsLanCigFmN8KojFhw.webp',
                'display_img' => 'storage/attornys/Anahita.webp',
                'about_head_one' => 'I JOINED THE COCHRAN FIRM',
                'about_head_two' => 'to become part of a team of attorneys who are second to none representing victims of all kinds.',
                'bio' => '<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgba(249,248,246,0.48); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: bold;">Anahita Sedaghatfar<span>&nbsp;</span></strong>practices general civil litigation in both state and federal courts. Ms. Sedaghatfar’s principal areas of practice include employment discrimination, sexual harassment, wrongful termination, entertainment law, and select criminal defense matters.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Ms. Sedaghatfar received her B.A. with highest honors in Political Science and Sociology with an emphasis on law in society from the University of California, Davis.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">She received her J.D., magna cum laude, from Southwestern University School of Law.</p><div class="content mCustomScrollbar _mCS_1" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><div class="mCustomScrollBox mCS-light" id="mCSB_1" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;"><div class="mCSB_container" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;"><div class="inPara" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;"><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">At Southwestern, Ms. Sedaghatfar served as a member of the Southwestern Law Review and was appointed to the Law Review’s Executive Board as a Note and Comment Editor. Ms. Sedaghatfar received several American Jurisprudence Awards for Academic Excellence, including awards for Professional Responsibility/Legal Ethics and Sports Law. Ms. Sedaghatfar also served as a judicial extern for the Honorable Audrey B. Collins, United States District Court for the Central District of California.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">Prior to starting her own law firm, Ms. Sedaghatfar was an associate in the Los Angeles office of Musick, Peeler &amp; Garrett, LLP where she practiced in the areas of products liability, business litigation and insurance coverage focusing on environmental litigation. Subsequently, Ms. Sedaghatfar established the Law Offices of Anahita Sedaghatfar and formed a partnership with famed O.J. Simpson prosecutor Christopher Darden. During this time, Ms. Sedaghatfar and Mr. Darden favorably litigated multiple sexual harassment and race, religion and age discrimination cases.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">Ms. Sedaghatfar has successfully represented both employers and employees with respect to lawsuits brought under the Fair Employment and Housing Act and wage and hour laws. She has counseled employers and companies regarding compliance with labor and employment laws and investigations of discrimination claims.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">In the entertainment realm, Ms. Sedaghatfar has experience with contract drafting, review and negotiation for professional athletes, independent film makers, actors, film distribution companies, prominent record labels and musicians.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">Throughout her career, Ms. Sedaghatfar has performed various pro bono services for indigent clients and for members of the California Lawyers for the Arts.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">In addition to maintaining her law practice, Ms. Sedaghatfar is an adjunct professor at Southwestern University School of Law and is a volunteer for Jewish Big Brothers Big Sisters of Los Angeles.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">Ms. Sedaghatfar was admitted to the State Bar of California in 2001 and is a member of the Los AngelesCounty and Beverly Hills Bar Associations.</p></div></div></div></div>',
                'created_at' => Carbon::now(),
                'updated_at' => Carbon::now(),
            ],
